The Police in Anambra State have arrested two armed robbery suspects, Ogbonna Chigozie and Chimezie Afulor, while attempting to escape into Abia State through one of the boundaries after a robbery operation in the state. The state Police Spokesperson, SP Haruna Mohammed, who disclosed this to journalists in Awka, Anambra State, said the suspected robbers were arrested on Thursday at about 5am by police operatives from Umuchu police division while on boundary patrol. “Today, being 14/05/2020 at about 5:23am, Police operatives attached to Umuchu Division in conjunction with patrol team from MOPOL 29 PMF Awka while enforcing the COVID-19 Curfew in Umuchu, Aguata LGA intercepted one Ogbonna Chigozie ‘m’ aged 18 years from Uturu, Abia State but resides at Nkpor in Idemili North LGA, and Chimezie Afulor ‘m’ aged 33years from Akirra Umunokpa, Uzowani LGA of Enugu State. “They were intercepted at the border post in Umuchu inside a tricycle with registration number GDD 081 VC conducting themselves in a suspicious manner.” He said the suspects were immediately searched and one locally made pistol with four rounds of life ammunition, one tricycle, house breaking implements and cash sum of N31,720 were found in them. “Preliminary investigation revealed that the suspects allegedly snatched the tricycle from Nkpor and were trying to cross to Akokwa in Imo State before their arrests.” He said the Commissioner of Police, CP John B.Abang, has ordered for immediate transfer of the case to the Command Special Anti Robbery Squard (SARS) for discreet investigation.